{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.12","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[{"sourceType":"competition","sourceId":125221,"databundleVersionId":16856040}],"dockerImageVersionId":31328,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":5,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"id":"42bacc16-5595-4f08-b2e2-868764798122","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# 🏎️ Predicting F1 Pit Stops — EDA + Strong LightGBM Baseline\n**Kaggle Playground Series S6E5** · Metric: **ROC-AUC** · Target: `PitNextLap` (will the driver pit on the *next* lap?)\n\nThis notebook is our **v1**: solid EDA + a competitive single-model LightGBM with proper cross-validation and a submission file. It is built around three findings from our data analysis:\n\n1. **`Normalized_TyreLife` is a leak.** In the original F1 dataset it equals `TyreLife / (driver's max tyre life in the race)` — i.e. *how far through your stint you are*, which hits 1.0 exactly on the lap before pitting. The organizers removed it because it makes the task trivial. **We never use it; instead we reconstruct a *legit, prior-based proxy*** (`tyre_life_ratio = TyreLife / expected_stint_length_for_compound`).\n2. **Tyre age is the engine of the signal.** Pit probability rises sharply as tyres age relative to their typical stint length. We engineer several features around this.\n3. **There is partial sequential structure** within each `(Driver, Race, Year)` sequence. We add lag features (previous-lap pit, lap-time change, degradation change) that observed-but-don't-leak the target.\n\n> **Accelerator: CPU is all you need for this notebook.** LightGBM trains fast on this data — no GPU/TPU required. (We'll switch to GPU later if we add neural nets.)\n","metadata":{}},{"id":"09b32ad4-73d7-4702-a8bb-f3e1302ed52d","cell_type":"code","source":"import os, gc, warnings, numpy as np, pandas as pd\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\nimport lightgbm as lgb\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import StratifiedKFold\nfrom sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\npd.set_option(\"display.max_columns\", 100)\n\nSEED      = 42\nN_SPLITS  = 5\nTARGET    = \"PitNextLap\"\nprint(\"LightGBM\", lgb.__version__)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T14:02:30.259680Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T14:02:30.260363Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-23T14:02:30.267039Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-23T14:02:30.260330Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-23T14:02:30.266159Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"LightGBM 4.6.0\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":3},{"id":"2966cd89-4528-4962-b6ef-dbb6e63ecff1","cell_type":"code","source":"# --- Load data (works on Kaggle and locally) ---\nCANDIDATES = [\"/kaggle/input/competitions/playground-series-s6e5\", \".\"]\nBASE = next((p for p in CANDIDATES if os.path.exists(os.path.join(p, \"train.csv\"))), \".\")\nprint(\"Reading from:\", BASE)\n\ntrain = pd.read_csv(f\"{BASE}/train.csv\")\ntest  = pd.read_csv(f\"{BASE}/test.csv\")\nsub   = pd.read_csv(f\"{BASE}/sample_submission.csv\")\nprint(\"train:\", train.shape, \"| test:\", test.shape)\ntrain.head()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T14:02:30.268518Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T14:02:30.268791Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-23T14:02:32.207784Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-23T14:02:30.268766Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-23T14:02:32.206935Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Reading from: /kaggle/input/competitions/playground-series-s6e5\ntrain: (439140, 16) | test: (188165, 15)\n","output_type":"stream"},{"execution_count":4,"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":"   id 