>\n</table>\n</div>"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":4},{"id":"a543040c-08a2-4624-aa86-99faec3f1ab8","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 1 · Exploratory Data Analysis\nJust enough to confirm the signal and guide feature engineering — we don't over-invest here.","metadata":{}},{"id":"1300314d-cff0-4a7a-b81c-b9a3eb7485b1","cell_type":"code","source":"# Target balance\nrate = train[TARGET].mean()\nprint(f\"Positive rate (pit next lap): {rate:.4f}  |  rows: {len(train):,}\")\nprint(\"\\nMissing values (train):\", train.isna().sum().sum(), \"| (test):\", test.isna().sum().sum())\nprint(\"\\nCompound counts:\\n\", train[\"Compound\"].value_counts())","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T14:02:32.208846Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T14:02:32.209177Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-23T14:02:32.357512Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-23T14:02:32.209142Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-23T14:02:32.356707Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Positive rate (pit next lap): 0.1990  |  rows: 439,140\n\nMissing values (train): 0 | (test): 0\n\nCompound counts:\n Compound\nMEDIUM          211141\nHARD            170518\nSOFT             38744\nINTERMEDIATE     17382\nWET               1355\nName: count, dtype: int64\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":5},{"id":"6bdaa0d8-6f5b-4d89-8981-20de8d9618b7","cell_type":"code","source":"# Pit-rate as a function of tyre age, race progress, compound, stint  --> the core hazard signals\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(13, 8))\n\n# (a) Pit rate vs TyreLife\ng = train.groupby(\"TyreLife\")[TARGET].agg([\"mean\",\"count\"])\ng = g[g[\"count\"] >= 50]\nax[0,0].plot(g.index, g[\"mean\"]); ax[0,0].set_title(\"Pit-next-lap rate vs TyreLife\")\nax[0,0].set_xlabel(\"TyreLife (laps)\"); ax[0,0].set_ylabel(\"P(pit next lap)\")\n\n# (b) Pit rate vs RaceProgress (binned)\ntmp = train.copy(); tmp[\"rp_bin\"] = (tmp[\"RaceProgress\"]*20).round()/20\ng = tmp.groupby(\"rp_bin\")[TARGET].mean()\nax[0,1].plot(g.index, g.values); ax[0,1].set_title(\"Pit rate vs RaceProgress\")\nax[0,1].set_xlabel(\"RaceProgress\"); ax[0,1].set_ylabel(\"P(pit next lap)\")\n\n# (c) Pit rate by Compound\ng = train.groupby(\"Compound\")[TARGET].mean().sort_values()\nax[1,0].bar(g.index, g.values); ax[1,0].set_title(\"Pit rate by Compound\"); ax[1,0].tick_params(axis=\"x\", rotation=20)\n\n# (d) Pit rate by Stint\ng = train.groupby(\"Stint\")[TARGET].mean()\nax[1,1].bar(g.index.astype(str), g.values); ax[1,1].set_title(\"Pit rate by Stint\")\nplt.tight_layout(); plt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T14:02:32.359087Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T14:02:32.359336Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-23T14:02:33.215361Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-23T14:02:32.359312Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-23T14:02:33.214456Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1300x800 with 4 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":6},{"id":"41baf85e-9f6e-4e6e-baba-93a311198cb8","cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Read-out:** pit probability climbs steeply with tyre age and peaks late in a stint; it differs by compound (softer tyres pit sooner) and rises with stint number. This is exactly the structure our engineered features will expose to the model.","metadata":{}},{"id":"70c2eee1-16b7-47ab-8d6d-07b272ebd852","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 2 · Feature Engineering\nAll features are computed identically for train and test. Key engineered features:\n- **`tyre_life_ratio`** — our legit proxy for the removed `Normalized_TyreLife`: `TyreLife / expected_stint_length(compound)`. Priors are learned from train (and are *not* future information).\n- **Race structure** — `race_len`, `laps_remaining`, `frac_remaining`.\n- **Degradation dynamics** — `deg_per_lap`, and within-sequence *changes* in lap time / tyre life / degradation.\n- **Lag features** — previous-lap `PitStop`, lap-time change, etc., computed within each `(Driver, Race, Year)` sequence. These use *observed* values only (never the target), so they are safe.\n- **Interactions** — `tyrelife_x_ratio`, `tyrelife_x_prog`, `stint_x_tyrelife`.\n- **`Driver` target encoding** is added later, *inside the CV loop*, to avoid leakage.","metadata":{}},{"id":"161b7c6e-964a-4a1e-abe4-0d90f3dd9c39","cell_type":"code","source":"COMP_ORD = {\"SOFT\":0, \"MEDIUM\":1, \"HARD\":2, \"INTERMEDIATE\":3, \"WET\":4}\n\n# ----- Priors learned from TRAIN (not leaky: these are population statistics) -----\n_sl = (train.sort_values([\"Driver\",\"Race\",\"Year\",\"Stint\",\"LapNumber\"])\n             .groupby([\"Driver\",\"Race\",\"Year\",\"Stint\"])\n             .agg(slen=(\"TyreLife\",\"max\"), comp=(\"Compound\",\"first\")).reset_index())\nCOMP_STINT = _sl.groupby(\"comp\")[\"slen\"].mean().to_dict()           # expected stint length per compound\nRACE_LEN   = (pd.concat([train[[\"Race\",\"Year\",\"LapNumber\"]], test[[\"Race\",\"Year\",\"LapNumber\"]]])\n                .groupby([\"Race\",\"Year\"])[\"LapNumber\"].max().to_dict())  # race length (known a priori)\nprint(\"Expected stint length by compound:\", {k: round(v,1) for k,v in COMP_STINT.items()})\n\ndef build_features(df):\n    df = df.copy()\n    df[\"comp_ord\"]        = df[\"Compound\"].map(COMP_ORD).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"comp_exp_stint\"]  = df[\"Compound\"].map(COMP_STINT).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"tyre_life_ratio\"] = (df[\"TyreLife\"] / df[\"comp_exp_stint\"]).astype(\"float32\")   # proxy normalized tyre life\n    df[\"race_len\"]        = df.set_index([\"Race\",\"Year\"]).index.map(RACE_LEN).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"laps_remaining\"]  = (df[\"race_len\"] - df[\"LapNumber\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"frac_remaining\"]  = (df[\"laps_remaining\"] / df[\"race_len\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"deg_per_lap\"]     = (df[\"Cumulative_Degradation\"] / (df[\"TyreLife\"] + 1)).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"tyrelife_x_prog\"] = (df[\"TyreLife\"] * df[\"RaceProgress\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"tyrelife_x_ratio\"]= (df[\"TyreLife\"] * df[\"tyre_life_ratio\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"stint_x_tyrelife\"]= (df[\"Stint\"] * df[\"TyreLife\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"pos_norm\"]        = (df[\"Position\"] / 20.0).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    # ----- sequential lag features within each (Driver, Race, Year) -----\n    df = df.sort_values([\"Driver\",\"Race\",\"Year\",\"LapNumber\"])\n    g = df.groupby([\"Driver\",\"Race\",\"Year\"], sort=False)\n    df[\"prev_pit\"]      = g[\"PitStop\"].shift(1)\n    df[\"laptime_chg\"]   = (df[\"LapTime (s)\"] - g[\"LapTime (s)\"].shift(1)).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"tyrelife_chg\"]  = (df[\"TyreLife\"] - g[\"TyreLife\"].shift(1)).astype(\"float32\")\n    df[\"deg_chg\"]       = (df[\"Cumulative_Degradation\"] - g[\"Cumulative_Degradation\"].shift(1)).astype(\"float32\")\n    # expanding mean lap time in the stint so far (how much slower than my own average?)\n    df[\"laptime_vs_avg\"]= (df[\"LapTime (s)\"] - g[\"LapTime (s)\"].transform(lambda s: s.expanding().mean())).astype(\"float32\")\n    return df\n\ntrain_fe = build_features(train)\ntest_fe  = build_features(test)\n\n# Race as a categorical code (LightGBM native categorical)\nrace_cats = pd.CategoricalDtype(categories=sorted(set(train[\"Race\"]) | set(test[\"Race\"])))\ntrain_fe[\"Race_cat\"] = train_fe[\"Race\"].astype(race_cats).cat.codes.astype(\"int32\")\ntest_fe[\"Race_cat\"]  = test_fe[\"Race\"].astype(race_cats).cat.codes.astype(\"int32\")\n\nNUM_FEATS = [\"comp_ord\",\"TyreLife\",\"Stint\",\"Position\",\"LapNumber\",\"RaceProgress\",\"Position_Change\",\n             \"LapTime (s)\",\"LapTime_Delta\",\"Cumulative_Degradation\",\"PitStop\",\"Year\",\n             \"comp_exp_stint\",\"tyre_life_ratio\",\"race_len\",\"laps_remaining\",\"frac_remaining\",\n             \"deg_per_lap\",\"tyrelife_x_prog\",\"tyrelife_x_ratio\",\"stint_x_tyrelife\",\"pos_norm\",\n             \"prev_pit\",\"laptime_chg\",\"tyrelife_chg\",\"deg_chg\",\"laptime_vs_avg\"]\nCAT_FEATS = [\"Race_cat\"]\nprint(f\"{len(NUM_FEATS)+len(CAT_FEATS)} base features (+ Driver target-encoding added in CV).\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T14:02:33.216477Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T14:02:33.216804Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-23T14:02:47.568832Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-05-23T14:02:33.216777Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-05-23T14:02:47.567993Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"Expected stint length by compound: {'HARD': 23.6, 'INTERMEDIATE': 17.2, 'MEDIUM': 17.9, 'SOFT': 14.3, 'WET': 13.8}\n28 base features (+ Driver target-encoding added in CV).\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":7},{"id":"2290dfb0-4ed7-45bc-aea6-7f849e8d8902","cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 3 · Cross-Validation + LightGBM\nWe use **StratifiedKFold (5 folds)** on the target. `Driver` target-encoding is computed **inside each fold** (fit on the fold's training rows only), so there is no leakage. Out-of-fold (OOF) predictions give us an honest AUC estimate, and test predictions are averaged across folds.","metadata":{}},{"id":"20733a73-5601-4ebc-b018-a0faa6376f3b","cell_type":"code","source":"def smoothed_te(frame, y, idx, col, m=50.0):\n    # Smoothed target encoding learned ONLY from rows in `idx` (no leakage).\n    sub_y = y[idx]\n    sub_c = frame[col].values[idx]\n    glob  = sub_y.mean()\n    dfm   = pd.DataFrame({col: sub_c, \"y\": sub_y})\n    agg   = dfm.groupby(col)[\"y\"].agg([\"mean\",\"count\"])\n    enc   = (agg[\"mean\"]*agg[\"count\"] + glob*m) / (agg[\"count\"] + m)\n    return enc.to_dict(), glob\n\ny      = train_fe[TARGET].values.astype(\"int8\")\ngroups = train_fe[\"Driver\"].values\nALL_FEATS = NUM_FEATS + CAT_FEATS + [\"Driver_te\"]\n\noof  = np.zeros(len(train_fe))\npred = np.zeros(len(test_fe))\nfold_aucs = []\nimportances = np.zeros(len(ALL_FEATS))\n\nparams = dict(objective=\"binary\", metric=\"auc\", boosting_type=\"gbdt\",\n              learning_rate=0.02, num_leaves=256, max_depth=-1,\n              feature_fraction=0.7, bagging_fraction=0.8, bagging_freq=1,\n              min_child_samples=60, lambda_l1=1.0, lambda_l2=2.0,\n              max_bin=255, verbose=-1, n_jobs=-1, seed=SEED)\n\nskf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=N_SPLITS, shuffle=True, random_state=SEED)\nfor fold, (tr_idx, va_idx) in enumerate(skf.split(train_fe, y)):\n    # in-fold target encoding for Driver\n    enc, glob = smoothed_te(train_fe, y, tr_idx, \"Driver\", m=50.0)\n    dtr_te = pd.Series(groups[tr_idx]).map(enc).fillna(glob).values\n    dva_te = pd.Series(groups[va_idx]).map(enc).fillna(glob).values\n    te_test = test_fe[\"Driver\"].map(enc).fillna(glob).values\n\n    Xtr = train_fe.iloc[tr_idx][NUM_FEATS+CAT_FEATS].copy(); Xtr[\"Driver_te\"] = dtr_te\n    Xva = train_fe.iloc[va_idx][NUM_FEATS+CAT_FEATS].copy(); Xva[\"Driver_te\"] = dva_te\n    Xte = test_fe[NUM_FEATS+CAT_FEATS].copy();               Xte[\"Driver_te\"] = te_test\n\n    dtr = lgb.Dataset(Xtr, y[tr_idx], categorical_feature=CAT_FEATS)\n    dva = lgb.Dataset(Xva, y[va_idx], categorical_feature=CAT_FEATS)\n    model = lgb.train(params, dtr, num_boost_round=5000, valid_sets=[dva],\n                      callbacks=[lgb.early_stopping(150), lgb.log_evaluation(0)])\n\n    oof[va_idx] = model.predict(Xva)\n    pred += model.predict(Xte) / N_SPLITS\n    importances += model.feature_importance(importance_type=\"gain\") / N_SPLITS\n    auc = roc_auc_score(y[va_idx], oof[va_idx])\n    fold_aucs.append(auc)\n    print(f\"Fold {fold+1}: AUC = {auc:.5f}  (best_iter {model.best_iteration})\")\n\noof_auc = roc_auc_score(y, oof)\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*46)\nprint(f\"  OOF AUC = {oof_auc:.5f}   (folds: {np.mean(fold_aucs):.5f} +/- {np.std(fold_aucs):.5f})\")\nprint(\"=\"*46)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-05-23T14:02:47.570000Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-05-23T14:02:47.570343Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-05-23T14: